WEBVTT

00:00:11.116 --> 00:00:15.120
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:00:17.872 --> 00:00:18.998
I knew they'd do it.

00:00:21.417 --> 00:00:22.919
-Hello, sir.
-Yeah.

00:00:25.505 --> 00:00:29.843
YEONSEO UNIVERSITY
PROGRAMMING COMPETITION RESULTS

00:00:34.222 --> 00:00:36.182
KIM SE-YUN, LEE KANG

00:00:36.766 --> 00:00:39.227
RUNNER-UP

00:00:42.480 --> 00:00:43.481
Mr. Heo.

00:00:44.065 --> 00:00:45.066
Jesus Christ!

00:00:45.150 --> 00:00:46.943
It's just me. Why are you so surprised?

00:00:48.653 --> 00:00:51.531
I was going to tell you,
but you've already seen.

00:00:55.243 --> 00:00:56.244
Hey.

00:00:57.036 --> 00:00:59.205
Why are you runner-up?
You knew the problems.

00:00:59.289 --> 00:01:03.459
I threw a few of the problems.
If we won, we'd be going to the finals.

00:01:04.377 --> 00:01:05.712
That wouldn't be fair.

00:01:09.257 --> 00:01:10.300
I'm going

00:01:10.800 --> 00:01:12.343
to Se-yun's house tomorrow.

00:01:12.844 --> 00:01:14.345
To have dinner with them.

00:01:15.305 --> 00:01:16.306
I was invited.

00:01:18.516 --> 00:01:19.350
I see.

00:01:20.143 --> 00:01:22.645
Then our lessons will start this weekend.

00:01:23.855 --> 00:01:25.899
Submit your assignment
by email before then.

00:01:25.982 --> 00:01:26.900
Okay.

00:01:27.400 --> 00:01:28.568
See you Saturday, then.

00:01:30.486 --> 00:01:31.487
Hey, Lee Kang.

00:01:38.536 --> 00:01:40.622
You do know this has to be our secret?

00:01:40.705 --> 00:01:42.415
It stays between us.

00:01:42.498 --> 00:01:43.583
I know.

00:02:01.392 --> 00:02:03.019
-Hello, sir.
-Yeah, hi!

00:02:04.646 --> 00:02:06.773
The act of writing itself helps you think…

00:02:06.856 --> 00:02:08.900
…no complete blueprint in your mind.

00:02:08.983 --> 00:02:11.319
It's akin to going on a journey
without a map.

00:02:13.655 --> 00:02:15.240
Yes, well…

00:02:15.323 --> 00:02:17.825
<i>If I push a large door open and enter,</i>

00:02:18.493 --> 00:02:20.411
<i>only to find another smaller door,</i>

00:02:20.995 --> 00:02:22.956
<i>did I ever really step inside,</i>

00:02:23.665 --> 00:02:25.416
<i>or was I outside all along?</i>

00:02:29.212 --> 00:02:30.380
A smaller door?

00:02:46.479 --> 00:02:47.313
How thoughtful.

00:02:48.731 --> 00:02:51.109
How did you know
that Yun's mom likes white roses?

00:02:51.776 --> 00:02:54.779
Yun told me, actually.

00:02:57.031 --> 00:02:58.783
But I could only afford three.

00:03:00.368 --> 00:03:02.412
How's the food? Do you like it?

00:03:02.495 --> 00:03:05.498
Yes, it's delicious.
I'm enjoying all of it.

00:03:05.581 --> 00:03:07.166
Thank you for inviting me.

00:03:07.667 --> 00:03:10.878
Not at all.
We should be the ones thanking you.

00:03:10.962 --> 00:03:13.423
Thanks to you, Kang, our Yun won an award.

00:03:13.506 --> 00:03:14.674
Runner-up, no less.

00:03:15.174 --> 00:03:17.468
We never expected that much.

00:03:17.969 --> 00:03:20.930
Please take good care of our Yun.

00:03:22.807 --> 00:03:24.767
Kang, do you have any siblings?

00:03:25.518 --> 00:03:26.352
Sorry?

00:03:29.272 --> 00:03:30.481
Oh, siblings?

00:03:31.190 --> 00:03:32.191
It's just me.

00:03:32.275 --> 00:03:33.735
So you're an only child.

00:03:34.235 --> 00:03:37.155
Where do your parents live?
What do they do?

00:03:40.408 --> 00:03:43.036
<i>A mother bird's anxious efforts</i>
<i>to protect her young.</i>

00:03:44.912 --> 00:03:46.581
<i>The second door I encountered.</i>

00:03:47.081 --> 00:03:49.334
Goodness, honey.

00:03:50.001 --> 00:03:51.627
Why would you ask him that?

00:03:52.920 --> 00:03:54.047
I just…

00:03:54.130 --> 00:03:57.133
Wait, was that rude of me?
Is it not okay to ask?

00:03:57.216 --> 00:04:00.428
Kang doesn't talk about himself much.
He doesn't like to.

00:04:00.928 --> 00:04:01.763
Is that so?

00:04:02.263 --> 00:04:06.017
I see. Then I guess that <i>was </i>rude of me.

00:04:06.100 --> 00:04:06.934
I'm sorry.

00:04:07.810 --> 00:04:08.978
My apologies.

00:04:09.854 --> 00:04:12.357
If we're all done eating,
should we have dessert?

00:04:12.440 --> 00:04:13.941
-Yeah.
-Fruit? Or cake?

00:04:15.026 --> 00:04:16.152
I don't have a mom.

00:04:21.074 --> 00:04:22.450
<i>I needed a key.</i>

00:04:22.992 --> 00:04:25.244
<i>A key that could unlock that door.</i>

00:04:25.328 --> 00:04:27.705
She left us when I was eight.

00:04:31.292 --> 00:04:34.545
My dad got hurt doing construction work
and was sick for a long time.

00:04:35.922 --> 00:04:38.758
He's in a nursing home now
due to alcohol-induced dementia.

00:04:42.428 --> 00:04:43.346
Then…

00:04:45.056 --> 00:04:46.682
who did you live with?

00:04:47.183 --> 00:04:48.893
-Honey.
-It's all right.

00:04:50.686 --> 00:04:51.771
I understand your curiosity.

00:04:54.148 --> 00:04:56.901
Yes, I'm asking
because I'm genuinely worried.

00:04:56.984 --> 00:04:58.945
I wonder who took care of him.

00:04:59.028 --> 00:05:00.905
Any parental figures.

00:05:01.864 --> 00:05:02.698
I did.

00:05:05.493 --> 00:05:06.744
I took care of myself

00:05:08.037 --> 00:05:09.122
and my dad.

00:05:12.417 --> 00:05:15.044
It was just us two
until he was hospitalized.

00:05:15.128 --> 00:05:18.423
From second grade
until I started university.

00:05:19.674 --> 00:05:21.175
Goodness.

00:05:21.676 --> 00:05:22.718
So,

00:05:23.761 --> 00:05:26.097
you studied while taking care of your dad

00:05:26.597 --> 00:05:28.224
and still got into Yeonseo?

00:05:28.891 --> 00:05:31.602
Kang's grades even got him
a full scholarship.

00:05:32.270 --> 00:05:33.271
Right?

00:05:33.354 --> 00:05:34.981
I worked really hard.

00:05:36.732 --> 00:05:38.693
I didn't want people to know my situation.

00:05:40.153 --> 00:05:42.530
Nor did I want to be a burden to anyone.

00:05:42.613 --> 00:05:46.325
So I studied like crazy
between my part-time jobs.

00:05:48.744 --> 00:05:50.955
But I don't feel alone anymore.

00:05:54.083 --> 00:05:55.626
Because I made a friend.

00:05:57.253 --> 00:05:59.297
Someone who's completely
different from me.

00:06:02.091 --> 00:06:04.010
He's so bright and carefree.

00:06:04.635 --> 00:06:08.431
Looking at him is like looking at
a clear blue sky without a single cloud.

00:06:10.600 --> 00:06:12.393
Yet he also has a big heart.

00:06:13.186 --> 00:06:15.188
At first, I was simply fascinated.

00:06:16.189 --> 00:06:18.232
Wondering how he grew up to be like that.

00:06:19.400 --> 00:06:21.652
But it clicked after I visited his home.

00:06:24.113 --> 00:06:26.240
Why he was so different.

00:06:29.535 --> 00:06:30.536
It was his family.

00:06:33.080 --> 00:06:34.916
Thanks to his loving family

00:06:35.833 --> 00:06:38.794
and thanks to him,
I think I'm starting to understand

00:06:40.463 --> 00:06:41.964
what makes a home

00:06:43.341 --> 00:06:44.884
and what family truly means.

00:06:47.512 --> 00:06:49.180
I'm learning a little every day.

00:06:54.769 --> 00:06:55.895
Oh my.

00:06:56.938 --> 00:06:58.439
Goodness, young man.

00:06:59.065 --> 00:07:02.151
You thought all that
every time you visited our home?

00:07:07.823 --> 00:07:10.785
You know what, Kang?
You're not alone anymore.

00:07:13.204 --> 00:07:14.705
Don't you understand?

00:07:15.206 --> 00:07:17.875
I'm saying you can come over
whenever you want.

00:07:18.751 --> 00:07:20.711
Consider this place your home.

00:07:21.587 --> 00:07:23.839
You're practically family now.

00:07:27.843 --> 00:07:30.012
<i>I only realized after opening the door</i>

00:07:30.763 --> 00:07:33.432
<i>which door it was</i>
<i>that I had truly wanted to open.</i>

00:07:36.769 --> 00:07:38.145
<i>The door to their hearts.</i>

00:07:38.854 --> 00:07:42.775
<i>Only then does the divide</i>
<i>between the inside and out disappear.</i>

00:07:46.320 --> 00:07:49.824
<i>P.S. I owe all of this to you, Mr. Heo.</i>

00:07:50.324 --> 00:07:52.535
<i>None of this would have been possible</i>

00:07:52.618 --> 00:07:54.870
<i>if you hadn't slipped me</i>
<i>the competition problems.</i>

00:07:55.746 --> 00:07:57.957
<i>Thank you, Mr. Heo.</i>

00:08:07.800 --> 00:08:11.220
What are you doing here? Why did you
read this without my permission?

00:08:12.763 --> 00:08:15.558
What was that about competition problems?

00:08:16.517 --> 00:08:20.021
You slipped him the problems?
What on earth did you do?

00:08:21.564 --> 00:08:22.898
What problems?

00:08:24.066 --> 00:08:25.443
What are you talking about?

00:08:25.943 --> 00:08:27.320
You don't know, do you?

00:08:27.862 --> 00:08:30.406
That you wrinkle your nose when you lie.

00:08:31.866 --> 00:08:34.368
Enough. I have a lot to do. Get out.

00:08:37.955 --> 00:08:40.625
Look. It's written right here at the end.

00:08:41.542 --> 00:08:43.085
-Let go.
-Hand it here.

00:08:45.671 --> 00:08:46.672
Are you insane?

00:08:46.756 --> 00:08:49.884
So why lie? What did he mean
about competition problems?

00:08:49.967 --> 00:08:51.218
Just drop it!

00:08:51.719 --> 00:08:52.845
What's it to you?

00:08:55.097 --> 00:08:56.307
"What's it to you?"

00:08:58.100 --> 00:08:59.310
Please.

00:08:59.393 --> 00:09:01.312
Just leave me alone.

00:09:01.395 --> 00:09:03.356
Stop trying to know everything.

00:09:04.231 --> 00:09:07.234
And from now on,
don't come in here without permission.

00:09:07.318 --> 00:09:08.986
Or read my students' assignments.

00:09:11.072 --> 00:09:13.240
Just mind your own business!

00:09:19.789 --> 00:09:23.042
That damn lunatic.
Why did he even write that?

00:09:38.516 --> 00:09:39.558
Oh my God!

00:09:43.104 --> 00:09:45.648
What are you doing? You startled me.

00:09:48.192 --> 00:09:49.527
I called your name.

00:09:50.361 --> 00:09:51.654
And knocked.

00:09:53.572 --> 00:09:54.407
What?

00:09:54.907 --> 00:09:55.991
Why are you here?

00:10:03.249 --> 00:10:04.709
What are you doing?

00:10:11.924 --> 00:10:14.343
I don't recall saying you could lie down.

00:10:22.727 --> 00:10:23.853
Yeah.

00:10:25.771 --> 00:10:27.690
I did something bad.

00:10:30.151 --> 00:10:31.527
Lee Kang, that punk.

00:10:32.528 --> 00:10:33.863
They were problems

00:10:33.946 --> 00:10:36.615
for his programming competition
or whatever.

00:10:38.617 --> 00:10:40.286
I stole them and gave them to him.

00:10:43.831 --> 00:10:45.374
Don't ask any more questions.

00:10:46.459 --> 00:10:48.544
I just had to do it, so I did.

00:10:49.462 --> 00:10:51.172
What's that supposed to mean?

00:10:51.922 --> 00:10:52.840
But how…

00:10:53.549 --> 00:10:54.842
How could you…

00:10:57.928 --> 00:11:01.932
Whatever the reason, this isn't like you.
Stealing competition problems?

00:11:02.016 --> 00:11:03.476
I know that too.

00:11:05.895 --> 00:11:07.730
It wasn't like me.

00:11:12.151 --> 00:11:13.319
But…

00:11:17.907 --> 00:11:19.033
it was thrilling.

00:11:20.326 --> 00:11:21.160
What?

00:11:23.120 --> 00:11:25.080
That's what made it even more thrilling.

00:11:26.707 --> 00:11:28.459
It was something I'd never do.

00:11:31.045 --> 00:11:32.713
I'd never felt like that before.

00:11:41.680 --> 00:11:42.890
<i>How should I put it?</i>

00:11:43.724 --> 00:11:48.270
<i>It felt like jumping over my own fence</i>
<i>for the first time in my life.</i>

00:11:56.320 --> 00:11:59.198
Are you saying crossing the line
made you feel liberated?

00:12:00.491 --> 00:12:02.076
Someone as bullheaded as you?

00:12:02.952 --> 00:12:04.286
Liberation? Please.

00:12:05.162 --> 00:12:07.081
That's just how it felt at the time.

00:12:10.334 --> 00:12:13.587
Come to think of it,
you have been acting a little strange.

00:12:14.421 --> 00:12:15.840
Even now.

00:12:16.924 --> 00:12:18.759
You're lying here on my bed.

00:12:27.977 --> 00:12:29.395
You can sleep here.

00:12:34.567 --> 00:12:38.237
If you want to sleep here, you can.
I don't mind.

00:13:00.801 --> 00:13:01.886
How long has it been…

00:13:04.722 --> 00:13:07.892
since we started sleeping
in separate rooms?

00:13:09.768 --> 00:13:11.312
How long?

00:13:13.063 --> 00:13:14.231
Twelve years?

00:13:15.149 --> 00:13:17.151
No, it's been 13 years.

00:13:20.654 --> 00:13:22.239
It was since then.

00:13:23.824 --> 00:13:25.576
When we gave up on IVF.

00:14:35.562 --> 00:14:37.731
Eat this with Lee Kang when he gets here.

00:14:37.815 --> 00:14:39.775
Today is your first real lesson, isn't it?

00:14:40.275 --> 00:14:41.527
Okay, thanks.

00:14:42.027 --> 00:14:43.654
You should head out now.

00:14:46.115 --> 00:14:49.660
No, I don't have anywhere to be today.
I'll stay here with you.

00:14:51.537 --> 00:14:54.873
-You don't mean in this room, do you?
-Is that a problem?

00:14:54.957 --> 00:14:57.918
Why would you be here for the lesson?

00:14:58.502 --> 00:15:01.797
Why are you getting so worked up?
I was just kidding.

00:15:07.720 --> 00:15:09.471
Why are you getting all awkward?

00:15:10.097 --> 00:15:12.266
-You won't even look at me.
-As if.

00:15:14.268 --> 00:15:16.311
You haven't changed a bit.

00:15:17.271 --> 00:15:18.939
Though I did always find it cute.

00:15:19.023 --> 00:15:22.192
Come on.
Stop talking nonsense and get out.

00:15:22.276 --> 00:15:24.028
He'll be here any minute.

00:15:26.071 --> 00:15:27.656
Wait, I have a question.

00:15:28.824 --> 00:15:32.786
Did you know about
what Lee Kang wrote in his assignment?

00:15:33.579 --> 00:15:35.164
About his personal life.

00:15:36.081 --> 00:15:38.667
I felt bad for him
while reading that part.

00:15:39.376 --> 00:15:43.047
I didn't. He and I have never
talked about that stuff before.

00:15:44.131 --> 00:15:46.133
Never? Not even once?

00:15:49.011 --> 00:15:50.846
That's the problem with you.

00:15:50.929 --> 00:15:54.475
You're a writer who teaches literature,
yet you don't care about people.

00:15:54.558 --> 00:15:55.642
What could he learn?

00:15:57.728 --> 00:15:59.021
Here we go again!

00:16:01.815 --> 00:16:02.649
Please leave.

00:16:36.475 --> 00:16:37.935
What's with the flowers?

00:16:38.602 --> 00:16:42.648
Since today's lesson is in the morning,
I figured your wife would be home.

00:16:43.148 --> 00:16:45.818
I couldn't show up empty-handed
the first time we met.

00:16:46.318 --> 00:16:48.028
But they were expensive.

00:16:48.779 --> 00:16:50.114
I could only afford three.

00:16:51.990 --> 00:16:53.200
Are you kidding me?

00:16:54.493 --> 00:16:58.330
You wrote that in your assignment
about the three white roses.

00:17:02.000 --> 00:17:03.293
Right, so I did.

00:17:04.419 --> 00:17:06.880
But it's true. Roses are expensive.

00:17:08.757 --> 00:17:09.758
Whatever.

00:17:11.718 --> 00:17:12.678
Let me ask.

00:17:14.721 --> 00:17:17.391
What you wrote about your life
in your assignment,

00:17:18.392 --> 00:17:19.226
is it true?

00:17:26.733 --> 00:17:29.820
Are you asking if the narrator
in my assignment and the author

00:17:30.362 --> 00:17:32.406
are the same person?

00:17:33.657 --> 00:17:34.658
Then what?

00:17:36.034 --> 00:17:37.119
You made that up?

00:17:38.912 --> 00:17:41.331
Not exactly, but I don't know.

00:17:42.624 --> 00:17:44.960
They could be the same
yet different, you know?

00:17:45.836 --> 00:17:48.881
Is the narrator in your novel
the same person as the author?

00:17:50.924 --> 00:17:51.758
My novel?

00:17:51.842 --> 00:17:52.885
Yes.

00:17:53.594 --> 00:17:54.469
Your novel.

00:18:04.938 --> 00:18:05.814
TWELVE WOMEN

00:18:06.148 --> 00:18:09.234
I stumbled upon it
at a secondhand bookstore.

00:18:10.152 --> 00:18:12.237
I haven't finished it yet,

00:18:13.030 --> 00:18:17.367
but it seems to be about a man
who wanders between 12 different women.

00:18:17.868 --> 00:18:19.661
Let's stop talking about this book.

00:18:22.164 --> 00:18:23.207
This book is…

00:18:25.042 --> 00:18:26.877
too complex for you to understand yet.

00:18:30.047 --> 00:18:32.132
Actually, no one can understand it.

00:18:32.633 --> 00:18:36.178
No. Although it's a bit complex,
I'm finding it interesting.

00:18:39.556 --> 00:18:43.602
So is the narrator in this novel
the same person as the author?

00:18:44.228 --> 00:18:45.062
Well?

00:18:48.023 --> 00:18:49.650
I'm dying to know.

00:19:01.787 --> 00:19:02.996
Yeah.

00:19:04.998 --> 00:19:06.333
Just as you said…

00:19:11.171 --> 00:19:14.132
the author and the narrator
can indeed be identical,

00:19:15.425 --> 00:19:16.927
or they can be different.

00:19:19.304 --> 00:19:21.014
The twelve women

00:19:22.391 --> 00:19:24.142
were mere figments of my imagination.

00:19:31.608 --> 00:19:33.819
The truth is, it was about one woman.

00:19:36.071 --> 00:19:36.905
Sorry?

00:19:37.990 --> 00:19:38.824
What was that?

00:19:38.907 --> 00:19:40.033
Enough.

00:19:41.743 --> 00:19:43.704
Let's stop talking about narrators.

00:19:44.788 --> 00:19:46.832
Let's start the lesson. Put that away.

00:19:47.457 --> 00:19:50.210
-No, what did you just say?
-Put it away, please.

00:19:56.300 --> 00:20:00.262
I actually have something to tell you
before we start the lesson.

00:20:01.763 --> 00:20:02.889
Some good news.

00:20:04.266 --> 00:20:06.018
I'm moving

00:20:07.144 --> 00:20:08.562
into Se-yun's house.

00:20:10.272 --> 00:20:11.189
Moving in?

00:20:19.031 --> 00:20:22.909
<i>It came up when we were eating</i>
<i>after a game of basketball.</i>

00:20:23.410 --> 00:20:25.537
-Move in?
-Yeah, move in.

00:20:27.414 --> 00:20:30.542
Ever since I heard about you
living in that budget micro-unit.

00:20:30.625 --> 00:20:31.793
It's been on my mind.

00:20:35.339 --> 00:20:37.883
Sorry, I told him about your place.

00:20:39.760 --> 00:20:43.055
You wouldn't be a burden,
so just come live with us, okay?

00:20:43.555 --> 00:20:46.933
His sister just happens to be moving out,
so we have a spare room.

00:20:47.476 --> 00:20:50.312
And Yun's mom is also on board, of course.

00:20:52.439 --> 00:20:55.609
As adults, it's our duty and reward

00:20:55.692 --> 00:20:58.153
to support smart kids like you.

00:20:59.321 --> 00:21:01.656
So don't worry about it.
Just move in, okay?

00:21:02.574 --> 00:21:03.450
Eat up.

00:21:04.618 --> 00:21:07.454
Consider it your home
and come live with us.

00:21:13.085 --> 00:21:13.960
And

00:21:15.545 --> 00:21:16.421
you agreed?

00:21:16.505 --> 00:21:17.714
Of course.

00:21:18.215 --> 00:21:20.175
Saving on rent is a huge deal for me.

00:21:21.218 --> 00:21:23.428
And it'd be good for our lessons too.

00:21:23.512 --> 00:21:25.889
I could write about
what I see and feel every day.

00:21:27.349 --> 00:21:32.854
Still, letting someone into their home
can't be an easy thing for them.

00:21:32.938 --> 00:21:37.401
You think I don't know that?
That's what makes Mr. Kim so amazing.

00:21:38.360 --> 00:21:40.278
Se-yun told me later

00:21:40.862 --> 00:21:43.615
that his mom only agreed
because his dad was so adamant.

00:21:44.950 --> 00:21:48.412
Se-yun says he respects his dad
more than anyone else in the world.

00:21:49.329 --> 00:21:50.997
He's strong yet considerate

00:21:51.915 --> 00:21:53.917
and has a young, flexible mindset.

00:21:55.168 --> 00:21:57.379
Mr. Kim is a really admirable guy.

00:21:59.798 --> 00:22:01.633
I think he's the first adult I've met…

00:22:04.136 --> 00:22:05.387
that I want to be like.

00:22:11.768 --> 00:22:14.855
You've got a long way to go
if you want to be a writer.

00:22:15.355 --> 00:22:16.189
Sorry?

00:22:16.273 --> 00:22:19.526
You're too hasty
to make up your mind about people.

00:22:19.609 --> 00:22:21.445
And your judgment is shallow and simple.

00:22:21.945 --> 00:22:24.990
You think he's great, amazing,
and you want to be like him

00:22:25.073 --> 00:22:27.200
just because of that one thing?

00:22:31.329 --> 00:22:32.414
All right, fine.

00:22:33.081 --> 00:22:35.500
You're still young,
so I guess it's understandable.

00:22:35.584 --> 00:22:36.751
But…

00:22:40.130 --> 00:22:41.840
you should know this.

00:22:43.300 --> 00:22:48.388
So far, you've only seen that man
and his family at a surface level.

00:22:48.889 --> 00:22:51.850
A perfect middle-class family
that lacks nothing.

00:22:52.350 --> 00:22:55.812
It's obvious and cliché.
A textbook example.

00:22:57.314 --> 00:23:00.859
Do you know why that is?
Because that's how you want to see them.

00:23:01.985 --> 00:23:03.778
That's what you want them to be.

00:23:07.908 --> 00:23:09.075
When it comes to people,

00:23:09.576 --> 00:23:11.328
what matters isn't who they are.

00:23:11.828 --> 00:23:14.873
It's their relationships.
That's what you need to look out for.

00:23:15.373 --> 00:23:18.126
That's the only way
to see their true selves.

00:23:20.754 --> 00:23:23.131
Since you've already decided to move in…

00:23:25.550 --> 00:23:26.843
for now…

00:23:29.095 --> 00:23:32.516
start with Mr. Kim
and study his various relationships.

00:23:32.599 --> 00:23:34.351
Observe them closely.

00:23:35.352 --> 00:23:36.937
This is your first assignment.

00:23:37.562 --> 00:23:38.688
Okay.

00:23:43.652 --> 00:23:44.486
Eat up.

00:23:47.405 --> 00:23:50.825
<i>Weren't you just envious of that dad?</i>

00:23:51.826 --> 00:23:53.245
What do you mean "envious"?

00:23:54.496 --> 00:23:55.413
Well,

00:23:55.914 --> 00:23:59.709
because Lee Kang kept complimenting him,

00:24:00.252 --> 00:24:02.796
saying he was the first adult
he wanted to be like.

00:24:03.296 --> 00:24:05.006
Maybe you were just envious.

00:24:05.632 --> 00:24:06.800
Am I wrong?

00:24:07.551 --> 00:24:08.426
Hey, wait.

00:24:08.927 --> 00:24:12.556
What do you take me for?
Do you think I'm that childish?

00:24:13.139 --> 00:24:16.017
If not, then fine.
That's just what it sounded like to me.

00:24:16.101 --> 00:24:18.979
Were you eavesdropping again?
How much did you hear?

00:24:19.479 --> 00:24:21.690
I didn't mean to listen in.

00:24:21.773 --> 00:24:23.942
I just caught bits here and there.

00:24:26.903 --> 00:24:29.823
I was just saying what needed to be said.

00:24:29.906 --> 00:24:34.286
He was being too one-sided,
so I restored balance, as his teacher.

00:24:35.120 --> 00:24:36.121
That's true.

00:24:36.621 --> 00:24:39.749
To someone who's starved for attention,
such kindness can feel huge.

00:24:39.833 --> 00:24:41.459
And it is a pretty big deal.

00:24:43.420 --> 00:24:45.130
You could try being nicer to him too.

00:24:45.630 --> 00:24:49.009
I know you want him
to look up to you as an adult.

00:24:50.260 --> 00:24:53.471
That Lee Kang kid is actually pretty cute.

00:24:53.555 --> 00:24:55.181
He has a peculiar charm.

00:24:59.311 --> 00:25:01.563
But doesn't he look familiar?

00:25:03.648 --> 00:25:05.483
Earlier, when I first saw him…

00:25:07.319 --> 00:25:08.695
Hello, nice to meet you.

00:25:10.322 --> 00:25:12.616
Oh my, you shouldn't have.

00:25:13.283 --> 00:25:15.368
It's nice to meet you. Come on in.

00:25:22.417 --> 00:25:23.251
I don't know.

00:25:31.509 --> 00:25:34.763
So did Lee Kang say
whether it was true or not?

00:25:35.263 --> 00:25:36.890
What he wrote in his assignment.

00:25:37.599 --> 00:25:39.726
Why are you so interested?

00:25:40.310 --> 00:25:41.561
Ever the therapist.

00:25:41.645 --> 00:25:43.188
I know, right?

00:25:43.772 --> 00:25:45.649
It keeps weighing on my mind.

00:25:46.566 --> 00:25:51.446
I wonder if his childhood was even harder
than his writing implies,

00:25:51.529 --> 00:25:52.614
given his deflection.

00:25:53.406 --> 00:25:55.575
Who knows what that kid is thinking?

00:25:56.993 --> 00:25:59.996
You don't think he'll do something strange
at that house, do you?

00:26:02.874 --> 00:26:05.293
Never mind. It's just the therapist in me.

00:26:05.919 --> 00:26:07.003
Something strange?

00:26:07.587 --> 00:26:08.463
Like what?

00:26:09.798 --> 00:26:12.759
Well, you know how people are.

00:26:13.677 --> 00:26:15.261
They can only endure

00:26:15.345 --> 00:26:19.182
because they have people
who believe in them and support them.

00:26:19.683 --> 00:26:23.895
And their sense of ethics tends to be
determined by those relationships.

00:26:24.604 --> 00:26:27.691
It seems like he hasn't had
anyone like that in his life.

00:26:29.192 --> 00:26:31.277
I'm just concerned.

00:26:32.362 --> 00:26:35.573
Lonely people can become
a dangerous presence

00:26:36.157 --> 00:26:38.535
when put in certain situations.

00:26:39.244 --> 00:26:40.453
It's sad.

00:26:44.708 --> 00:26:46.209
A dangerous presence?

00:26:47.210 --> 00:26:48.128
Yes.

00:26:49.546 --> 00:26:50.797
What are you doing?

00:26:51.589 --> 00:26:54.050
Mr. Heo, look here.

00:26:54.134 --> 00:26:57.262
I made this game. Want to take a look?

00:26:58.763 --> 00:27:02.600
You press down to move forward
and double-click to do this.

00:28:00.867 --> 00:28:02.118
Some dream.

00:28:16.299 --> 00:28:18.593
Hello, I'm Lee Kang--

00:28:31.606 --> 00:28:34.234
There you are.
Well done for making it here.

00:28:34.734 --> 00:28:35.652
Here. Let me.

00:28:36.152 --> 00:28:38.696
<i>The reason a trip is considered a trip…</i>

00:28:44.619 --> 00:28:46.454
<i>is because you have a home to return to.</i>

00:28:57.423 --> 00:28:58.842
But this is your sister's room.

00:28:58.925 --> 00:29:02.762
I told you she moved out.
She only comes home a few times a year.

00:29:03.471 --> 00:29:04.430
It's your room now.

00:29:07.100 --> 00:29:07.934
All yours.

00:29:16.317 --> 00:29:19.362
Are you sure you'll be okay here?
We don't even use this room.

00:29:20.154 --> 00:29:21.281
It's fine.

00:29:23.283 --> 00:29:25.702
We should clear some of the junk out.

00:29:26.494 --> 00:29:29.330
<i>And because you have</i>
<i>your own room to return to.</i>

00:29:30.039 --> 00:29:32.584
I thought it'd upset her
if her room was gone.

00:29:32.667 --> 00:29:35.962
It was an easy decision
when I put myself in her shoes.

00:29:37.088 --> 00:29:38.798
Goodness, how sweet of you.

00:29:38.882 --> 00:29:40.884
And you're so considerate.

00:29:40.967 --> 00:29:42.760
You've never even met her.

00:29:43.553 --> 00:29:47.056
It's still a hundred times better
than my old place. I couldn't be happier.

00:29:47.724 --> 00:29:49.517
All right, then. A welcome toast.

00:29:50.810 --> 00:29:51.728
Lee Kang,

00:29:52.312 --> 00:29:53.813
welcome to the family.

00:29:53.897 --> 00:29:55.231
Welcome.

00:29:55.315 --> 00:29:56.524
Welcome!

00:29:59.277 --> 00:30:00.820
Speak of the devil.

00:30:01.321 --> 00:30:03.281
-It's Jeong-hu.
-Of course it is.

00:30:05.283 --> 00:30:07.452
I'm so nice,
I'm letting you keep your room.

00:30:08.161 --> 00:30:10.914
<i>Whatever. I told you I don't care.</i>

00:30:11.414 --> 00:30:14.500
<i>This is my room and my home now.</i>

00:30:14.584 --> 00:30:15.627
There you go again.

00:30:15.710 --> 00:30:18.922
You're going to make your dad cry.
He'll start crying from heartbreak.

00:30:19.005 --> 00:30:21.257
That's right, kid.
You're not family anymore.

00:30:21.883 --> 00:30:23.760
Just say hi. This is my friend.

00:30:24.510 --> 00:30:26.137
-<i>Lee Kang?</i>
-Hello.

00:30:27.805 --> 00:30:31.601
<i>Hey. Yun's told me so much about you.</i>
<i>I feel like we've already met.</i>

00:30:33.186 --> 00:30:34.896
<i>-See you around.</i>
-Sure.

00:30:35.813 --> 00:30:38.107
-Don't skip any meals.
-Bye.

00:30:38.191 --> 00:30:41.819
<i>It's because you have people</i>
<i>who welcome you when you're back.</i>

00:30:42.320 --> 00:30:43.529
<i>Dad!</i>

00:30:43.613 --> 00:30:45.615
<i>Does that mean I can now</i>

00:30:46.240 --> 00:30:47.951
<i>go on a trip too?</i>

00:30:49.369 --> 00:30:52.664
<i>Can I finally set off on a trip of my own?</i>

00:31:11.683 --> 00:31:13.601
What are you looking at, jerk?

00:31:13.685 --> 00:31:15.937
Thanks to you, I now have more work to do.

00:31:24.779 --> 00:31:27.198
<i>The one person</i>
<i>who's ruining the thrill of a new trip.</i>

00:31:31.369 --> 00:31:33.663
I heard you lived in a budget micro-unit<i>.</i>

00:31:34.956 --> 00:31:36.332
Guess you struck gold.

00:31:45.466 --> 00:31:46.718
<i>Her name is Seon Min-hui.</i>

00:31:46.801 --> 00:31:48.761
<i>She's in her early-thirties, maybe?</i>

00:31:48.845 --> 00:31:50.972
<i>She comes to work three times a week.</i>

00:31:59.397 --> 00:32:00.815
Oh my gosh! Oh dear.

00:32:01.858 --> 00:32:02.984
Sorry.

00:32:03.067 --> 00:32:04.777
You should be more careful.

00:32:04.861 --> 00:32:06.279
It's okay. I'll do it.

00:32:12.785 --> 00:32:16.330
<i>She's the only person</i>
<i>who hates that I moved into this house.</i>

00:32:16.414 --> 00:32:20.501
You can't throw your cigarette butts
in the flower bed. This is yours, right?

00:32:21.419 --> 00:32:22.670
It isn't.

00:32:23.379 --> 00:32:24.714
It's not mine, it's his.

00:32:24.797 --> 00:32:27.091
You know, that friend of Se-yun's.
Lee Kang.

00:32:27.633 --> 00:32:28.593
I saw him do it.

00:32:29.093 --> 00:32:32.555
What are you talking about?
Now you're even telling lies?

00:32:32.638 --> 00:32:35.516
Here, there's clearly lipstick on it.

00:32:36.225 --> 00:32:38.227
Besides, our kids don't smoke.

00:32:39.520 --> 00:32:43.066
As smoking is a preference,
I can't do anything about it, but still.

00:32:43.733 --> 00:32:46.110
I don't want anyone smoking in my home.

00:32:46.611 --> 00:32:48.196
It's bad for the flowers too.

00:32:49.530 --> 00:32:51.115
Please don't, okay?

00:32:59.791 --> 00:33:00.625
What?

00:33:01.417 --> 00:33:03.044
Bad for the flowers, you say?

00:33:43.084 --> 00:33:45.128
<i>Just hire someone else.</i>

00:33:45.211 --> 00:33:47.004
Why are you putting up with her?

00:33:47.505 --> 00:33:49.590
I can tell her for you
if you find it hard.

00:33:50.091 --> 00:33:51.217
Oh, I don't know.

00:33:52.552 --> 00:33:54.595
I don't know what to do with her.

00:33:55.096 --> 00:33:57.640
I felt bad for her
because she's a single mother.

00:33:58.558 --> 00:34:00.810
But if I fire her,

00:34:01.310 --> 00:34:04.147
I couldn't face the president
of our church's volunteer group.

00:34:04.230 --> 00:34:05.857
They introduced her to me.

00:34:06.774 --> 00:34:11.028
You're overthinking things so much,
it's making you cranky.

00:34:12.029 --> 00:34:12.905
Legs here.

00:34:17.368 --> 00:34:18.703
Still,

00:34:20.204 --> 00:34:21.998
she might be a bit unruly,

00:34:22.623 --> 00:34:25.001
but her side dishes are incredible.

00:34:25.751 --> 00:34:28.838
Our Yun devours
all the side dishes Min-hui makes.

00:34:29.755 --> 00:34:30.756
That's good.

00:34:31.257 --> 00:34:34.177
That feels so good. That's the spot.

00:34:34.260 --> 00:34:35.094
Here?

00:34:35.761 --> 00:34:36.888
I'm good at this, right?

00:34:37.471 --> 00:34:38.556
You sure are.

00:34:39.182 --> 00:34:41.058
You get better by the day.

00:34:42.351 --> 00:34:43.978
You're as good as any masseuse.

00:34:50.276 --> 00:34:51.444
So,

00:34:52.111 --> 00:34:53.779
please don't think too much.

00:34:53.863 --> 00:34:56.199
Don't let useless thoughts
clutter your mind, okay?

00:34:57.700 --> 00:35:01.412
The most important thing to me
is that you feel at peace, okay?

00:35:02.246 --> 00:35:03.331
In our family,

00:35:04.498 --> 00:35:06.667
nothing matters more than that.

00:35:07.710 --> 00:35:10.004
Oh, all right.

00:35:10.087 --> 00:35:12.298
I can't say anything to you
without you worrying.

00:36:00.137 --> 00:36:01.806
You know the kids are home, right?

00:36:02.306 --> 00:36:03.808
So what if they are?

00:36:38.175 --> 00:36:39.010
You didn't…

00:36:41.721 --> 00:36:43.222
listen in on that, did you?

00:36:44.307 --> 00:36:45.808
No, Se-yun called me

00:36:46.851 --> 00:36:48.394
not long after that.

00:36:54.108 --> 00:36:56.193
Why do you look so disappointed?

00:36:56.736 --> 00:36:57.570
Sorry?

00:37:01.615 --> 00:37:02.450
Hey.

00:37:02.950 --> 00:37:04.076
Don't.

00:37:05.244 --> 00:37:07.371
That's voyeurism, you know.

00:37:08.622 --> 00:37:11.709
I told you to be an observer,
not a voyeur.

00:37:12.752 --> 00:37:13.961
That's unacceptable.

00:37:15.338 --> 00:37:16.464
What's the difference?

00:37:16.547 --> 00:37:17.882
The difference, you punk…

00:37:19.884 --> 00:37:20.843
Hold on.

00:37:30.603 --> 00:37:31.896
What are you doing?

00:37:39.862 --> 00:37:42.406
Deliberately spying on
and eavesdropping on people.

00:37:42.490 --> 00:37:46.577
Anyway, the moment you start
indulging in it, it becomes voyeurism.

00:37:47.703 --> 00:37:49.622
I didn't see them on purpose.

00:37:50.498 --> 00:37:51.832
It just happened.

00:37:53.292 --> 00:37:54.668
You sly bastard.

00:37:56.003 --> 00:37:57.838
Do you honestly think that's believable?

00:38:00.049 --> 00:38:02.343
Absolutely not. Observation only.

00:38:03.969 --> 00:38:07.431
Anyway, Mr. Kim really loves his wife.

00:38:07.515 --> 00:38:09.058
That's my point.

00:38:09.141 --> 00:38:11.143
From what I've observed,

00:38:12.728 --> 00:38:15.439
the two of them
frequently share small touches.

00:38:15.940 --> 00:38:19.735
Do you think two people being touchy-feely
always means it's love?

00:38:19.819 --> 00:38:21.737
If it's not love, what is it?

00:38:21.821 --> 00:38:26.283
Okay, yeah. You're still young,
so you might see that as love.

00:38:26.784 --> 00:38:30.037
But you see, with married couples…

00:38:34.125 --> 00:38:37.253
it could very well be a desperate attempt

00:38:38.462 --> 00:38:40.631
to overcome the cold tedium

00:38:42.216 --> 00:38:43.634
that has settled over time.

00:38:43.717 --> 00:38:46.137
What am I even saying right now?

00:38:48.389 --> 00:38:51.684
Anyway, married couples
are complicated, okay?

00:38:52.184 --> 00:38:53.769
Are you talking about yourself?

00:38:55.521 --> 00:38:56.355
What?

00:38:57.523 --> 00:39:00.985
Well, I'm just wondering
how things are with you and your wife.

00:39:02.153 --> 00:39:04.613
Why are you curious about that?

00:39:06.407 --> 00:39:07.366
You little punk.

00:39:07.867 --> 00:39:10.578
You stepped on the line. Don't cross it.

00:39:14.248 --> 00:39:18.085
Hey, tell me more about that housekeeper.

00:39:18.169 --> 00:39:19.670
No, I don't want to.

00:39:20.588 --> 00:39:22.214
I don't want to talk about her.

00:39:22.298 --> 00:39:23.549
Why not?

00:39:24.842 --> 00:39:26.260
Does she keep harassing you?

00:39:27.595 --> 00:39:29.638
Tell me about you instead. Please?

00:39:31.765 --> 00:39:32.683
Do the two of you…

00:39:34.935 --> 00:39:36.103
love each other?

00:39:36.645 --> 00:39:40.316
How do we seem to you?
Do we look like we're in love?

00:39:40.399 --> 00:39:42.776
Why would you ask something like that?

00:39:42.860 --> 00:39:45.529
You're talking nonsense
and to a little kid at that.

00:39:46.030 --> 00:39:48.782
What do you mean "a little kid"?
He's an adult now.

00:39:49.283 --> 00:39:52.453
And he's at the age where he'd be curious
about these things, right?

00:39:53.621 --> 00:39:56.916
It seems like you love Mr. Heo,

00:39:58.375 --> 00:40:00.085
but I'm not sure about Mr. Heo.

00:40:03.005 --> 00:40:06.634
You're right.
I always wonder about him too.

00:40:07.551 --> 00:40:09.011
You tell me. Do you love me?

00:40:11.847 --> 00:40:12.848
Hey.

00:40:12.932 --> 00:40:14.683
Stop eating. Put that down.

00:40:16.143 --> 00:40:18.896
What are you doing?
Our lesson ended ages ago.

00:40:18.979 --> 00:40:19.813
Hurry on home.

00:40:19.897 --> 00:40:23.609
What's your deal?
I ordered this specifically for Kang.

00:40:24.109 --> 00:40:25.486
Take your time and eat up.

00:40:26.237 --> 00:40:27.655
You should have some too.

00:40:29.240 --> 00:40:30.241
You too, Mr. Heo.

00:40:30.324 --> 00:40:31.450
I am.

00:40:34.370 --> 00:40:37.957
Then maybe I'll try a piece too.

00:40:40.125 --> 00:40:42.419
No, I need to lose weight.

00:40:42.920 --> 00:40:44.547
You're trying to lose weight?

00:40:45.214 --> 00:40:47.341
But you're already so beautiful.

00:40:47.841 --> 00:40:49.093
Oh my, is that right?

00:40:52.471 --> 00:40:55.849
Thank you. You're the only one
who compliments me like that.

00:40:58.352 --> 00:41:00.062
What a load of crap.

00:41:05.818 --> 00:41:09.738
The truth is,
I think Mr. Heo loves you too.

00:41:10.239 --> 00:41:12.992
Maybe his love is so deep
that it's invisible.

00:41:13.075 --> 00:41:14.118
You think so?

00:41:14.868 --> 00:41:16.412
What makes you think that?

00:41:17.788 --> 00:41:19.832
I finished reading Mr. Heo's book.

00:41:21.750 --> 00:41:25.838
After reading it,
I realized who the one woman is.

00:41:28.007 --> 00:41:29.008
The one woman?

00:41:29.717 --> 00:41:31.760
Mr. Heo told me in a previous lesson

00:41:32.261 --> 00:41:36.682
that the 12 women are just symbolic,
and it's actually about one woman.

00:41:36.765 --> 00:41:37.891
When did I say that?

00:41:38.851 --> 00:41:39.768
When did I say that?

00:41:40.269 --> 00:41:41.562
You said that.

00:41:42.187 --> 00:41:44.648
You said it quietly,
but I definitely heard you.

00:41:45.149 --> 00:41:46.400
I'm guessing that one woman

00:41:47.651 --> 00:41:49.862
is Ms. Jo, of course.

00:41:51.196 --> 00:41:52.031
Right?

00:41:56.368 --> 00:41:57.494
One woman?

00:42:12.384 --> 00:42:16.347
Hey, don't pay any mind
to what that kid said as a joke.

00:42:16.430 --> 00:42:19.141
That kid was just spouting nonsense.

00:42:19.224 --> 00:42:20.392
Don't worry about it.

00:42:20.893 --> 00:42:22.519
Worry? Please.

00:42:23.103 --> 00:42:25.648
Your age-old first love? What a laugh.

00:42:28.067 --> 00:42:29.318
What? First love?

00:42:30.527 --> 00:42:31.862
It's that woman.

00:42:31.945 --> 00:42:35.741
The name that keeps coming up
in your old draft notes.

00:42:36.367 --> 00:42:37.660
It must be her.

00:42:38.452 --> 00:42:40.829
That's all in the past. Ancient history.

00:42:41.455 --> 00:42:43.499
What does any of that matter now?

00:42:44.333 --> 00:42:46.251
Yeah, I didn't say anything about it.

00:42:47.753 --> 00:42:48.671
Still,

00:42:49.546 --> 00:42:52.841
I didn't know all 12 women were her.

00:42:53.592 --> 00:42:58.305
Then again, what do I even know about you?

00:43:09.108 --> 00:43:10.067
Lee Kang.

00:43:10.567 --> 00:43:12.444
That little smart-ass, I swear…

00:43:16.990 --> 00:43:19.993
<i>It doesn't always take a typhoon</i>
<i>to sway a tree.</i>

00:43:24.206 --> 00:43:26.250
<i>Some trees can be uprooted</i>

00:43:26.750 --> 00:43:28.836
<i>with a mere passing breeze.</i>

00:43:30.087 --> 00:43:32.923
Why do you keep suspecting me?

00:43:33.006 --> 00:43:35.676
I told you, I didn't steal it!

00:43:35.759 --> 00:43:38.679
Why are you lying to me again
when I found it right here?

00:43:38.762 --> 00:43:41.098
Then how else would it have
ended up in here?

00:43:41.598 --> 00:43:43.517
How should I know?

00:43:44.226 --> 00:43:45.269
And also,

00:43:46.103 --> 00:43:48.439
why would you go through my bag
without permission?

00:43:49.773 --> 00:43:51.900
I'm sorry about that.

00:43:52.401 --> 00:43:54.486
But do you really think I wanted to look?

00:43:54.570 --> 00:43:56.822
I searched everywhere.
I was at my wits' end!

00:43:56.905 --> 00:43:59.700
Why is it pouring all of a sudden?

00:44:03.036 --> 00:44:07.040
So what if your damn scarf is designer?

00:44:09.084 --> 00:44:12.629
If you keep doubting me like this,

00:44:13.422 --> 00:44:15.382
I won't be able to work here anymore.

00:44:16.842 --> 00:44:17.676
I quit.

00:44:25.684 --> 00:44:27.352
What's the matter this time?

00:44:27.853 --> 00:44:28.812
Well,

00:44:29.313 --> 00:44:30.981
Min-hui stole my new scarf…

00:44:31.899 --> 00:44:33.650
Mom!

00:44:34.777 --> 00:44:35.694
Are you okay?

00:44:36.195 --> 00:44:38.906
-Should I bring you your sedatives?
-Yeah, get me my meds.

00:44:38.989 --> 00:44:40.157
Yeah, okay.

00:44:43.827 --> 00:44:47.915
This is why I told you not to stress
and just hire someone else!

00:44:49.792 --> 00:44:50.959
Damn it.

00:44:52.252 --> 00:44:54.296
That's it. I'll have a firm word with her.

00:44:54.379 --> 00:44:55.589
Honey…

00:45:01.053 --> 00:45:02.429
Are you out of your mind?

00:45:06.308 --> 00:45:10.312
You've gone beyond being a voyeur
and are actually messing with them now?

00:45:12.147 --> 00:45:13.065
You're telling me

00:45:14.566 --> 00:45:16.610
you snuck the scarf in her bag?

00:45:19.071 --> 00:45:20.405
I did,

00:45:20.906 --> 00:45:22.699
but she messed with me first.

00:45:22.783 --> 00:45:25.702
She spilled drinks on me on purpose
and kept belittling me.

00:45:25.786 --> 00:45:27.746
You think this is on the same level?

00:45:28.705 --> 00:45:29.540
So, what?

00:45:30.249 --> 00:45:31.917
You wanted to get her fired?

00:45:32.793 --> 00:45:34.962
No, I was just pulling a prank--

00:45:35.045 --> 00:45:37.589
A prank? What do you mean "prank"?

00:45:39.049 --> 00:45:40.259
What you did

00:45:41.093 --> 00:45:43.095
was frame someone as a thief.

00:45:44.012 --> 00:45:45.055
You crossed a line.

00:45:49.017 --> 00:45:50.853
I wouldn't have done that

00:45:51.478 --> 00:45:53.188
if she hadn't messed with me.

00:45:58.986 --> 00:46:00.487
You punk, you really…

00:46:00.988 --> 00:46:03.907
You go around causing trouble
with every family you visit!

00:46:06.368 --> 00:46:07.369
Every family?

00:46:12.040 --> 00:46:13.792
Look, kid, what I mean is…

00:46:14.710 --> 00:46:16.795
I told you over and over again, didn't I?

00:46:17.379 --> 00:46:22.926
I told you to observe relationships,
not to go around sparking conflict.

00:46:23.010 --> 00:46:24.011
Right?

00:46:24.761 --> 00:46:26.805
Meddling and starting arguments.

00:46:27.764 --> 00:46:29.433
A writer shouldn't do that.

00:46:32.102 --> 00:46:36.023
After our last lesson, did you argue
with your wife because of what I…

00:46:38.567 --> 00:46:40.402
Is that why we're here today for--

00:46:40.485 --> 00:46:44.197
Argue? We didn't argue!
Don't act like you know everything!

00:46:48.201 --> 00:46:49.119
Anyway,

00:46:49.995 --> 00:46:52.497
our lessons will take place here
from now on. Period.

00:46:53.582 --> 00:46:54.416
Yes, sir.

00:46:57.544 --> 00:46:59.254
Man, I'm exhausted.

00:47:00.172 --> 00:47:02.716
Let's call it a day.
We'll continue next time.

00:47:07.971 --> 00:47:09.097
But, Mr. Heo,

00:47:09.806 --> 00:47:11.183
I learned a shocking truth.

00:47:11.266 --> 00:47:14.144
I was going to write it,
but I wanted to tell you in person.

00:47:17.272 --> 00:47:19.191
You were right, Mr. Heo.

00:47:20.525 --> 00:47:22.903
You can't judge a person by what you see.

00:47:23.779 --> 00:47:24.780
Keep it short.

00:47:25.656 --> 00:47:28.283
There's something going on
between Mr. Kim and Min-hui.

00:47:32.162 --> 00:47:32.996
That day…

00:47:34.623 --> 00:47:36.291
I saw them that day.

00:47:43.173 --> 00:47:47.469
<i>Mr. Kim stepped outside, saying he'd have</i>
<i>a firm word with Min-hui, but…</i>

00:48:08.991 --> 00:48:10.909
<i>they looked like a couple.</i>

00:48:13.912 --> 00:48:18.041
Then Se-yun's dad grabbed her,
and they went into the garage.

00:48:18.125 --> 00:48:21.253
So I secretly followed them,
and I saw… I saw…

00:48:43.567 --> 00:48:45.610
the car was shaking.

00:48:45.694 --> 00:48:47.988
Shaking like this.
What else could that mean?

00:48:48.071 --> 00:48:49.072
Hey!

00:48:52.617 --> 00:48:54.119
Is this why you moved in?

00:48:54.619 --> 00:48:57.289
To spy on them and make assumptions?

00:48:57.789 --> 00:49:01.460
Do you think I'm giving you these lessons
so I can listen to this bullshit?

00:49:01.543 --> 00:49:03.587
No, I really saw it!

00:49:03.670 --> 00:49:05.005
You saw it? Really?

00:49:05.088 --> 00:49:07.799
You said you felt dizzy that day.
Are you sure you saw that?

00:49:07.883 --> 00:49:09.509
Yes, of course I saw…

00:49:15.766 --> 00:49:16.641
Lee Kang.

00:49:17.768 --> 00:49:19.311
What you're saying right now

00:49:19.853 --> 00:49:25.067
is no different from indiscriminately
swinging a hammer at people.

00:49:25.567 --> 00:49:27.069
Just like in that game you made.

00:49:27.152 --> 00:49:29.780
That unethical
and irresponsible attitude of yours.

00:49:29.863 --> 00:49:32.407
Caring only for entertainment
regardless of the truth!

00:49:35.827 --> 00:49:36.912
But the thing is…

00:49:38.955 --> 00:49:40.749
literature is not a game.

00:49:42.751 --> 00:49:45.796
Your attitude must be sincere.
That's of the utmost importance.

00:49:48.924 --> 00:49:50.634
In order to write a good story,

00:49:52.219 --> 00:49:54.054
you have to be a decent human being.

00:49:56.765 --> 00:49:57.599
Got it?

00:50:07.901 --> 00:50:09.694
I think you were right.

00:50:16.451 --> 00:50:17.661
Lee Kang, that punk.

00:50:19.496 --> 00:50:22.415
I think there's something off
about that bastard.

00:50:23.291 --> 00:50:25.001
I think I need to stop the lessons.

00:50:29.422 --> 00:50:32.425
Isn't that why you liked him?
Because he was stimulating?

00:50:33.260 --> 00:50:34.594
I quite like him.

00:50:36.012 --> 00:50:37.347
What the heck?

00:50:38.265 --> 00:50:40.350
You said he was dangerous and all that.

00:50:42.144 --> 00:50:43.812
That was your takeaway?

00:50:44.896 --> 00:50:46.565
Such poor comprehension skills.

00:50:46.648 --> 00:50:47.482
What?

00:50:48.400 --> 00:50:50.443
I was just briefly worried.

00:50:51.361 --> 00:50:53.029
But I'm not worried anymore.

00:50:53.905 --> 00:50:56.241
He seems more normal than you.

00:51:00.912 --> 00:51:02.956
What? Are you still…

00:51:04.332 --> 00:51:05.917
Am I still what?

00:51:06.459 --> 00:51:08.879
I have a lot of reports to write.
Please leave.

00:51:53.673 --> 00:52:00.680
LEE KANG

00:52:12.943 --> 00:52:13.777
What is it?

00:52:14.277 --> 00:52:15.487
<i>Were you sleeping?</i>

00:52:15.987 --> 00:52:18.365
<i>I'm so sorry, but I got into an accident.</i>

00:52:18.949 --> 00:52:21.034
<i>I need a guardian, so could you…</i>

00:52:21.743 --> 00:52:23.495
<i>Could you please come here?</i>

00:52:23.995 --> 00:52:25.413
What? An accident?

00:52:25.914 --> 00:52:29.751
<i>You'll get the details when you're here.</i>
<i>It's urgent, so please hurry.</i>

00:52:31.544 --> 00:52:32.629
But

00:52:33.255 --> 00:52:34.422
why did you contact me?

00:52:34.506 --> 00:52:36.716
<i>You were the first person</i>
<i>who came to mind.</i>

00:52:36.800 --> 00:52:38.426
<i>I could have called Mr. Kim,</i>

00:52:39.010 --> 00:52:42.097
<i>but still, I'd like for you to come.</i>

00:52:48.603 --> 00:52:50.730
Fine. Where are you?

00:53:19.634 --> 00:53:20.552
What's going on?

00:53:24.431 --> 00:53:26.016
What accident, exactly?

00:53:27.600 --> 00:53:28.601
I'm sorry.

00:53:29.686 --> 00:53:30.770
The truth is…

00:53:35.608 --> 00:53:36.651
Did you lie to me?

00:53:36.735 --> 00:53:38.403
I'll tell you everything.

00:53:38.486 --> 00:53:39.529
The truth is…

00:53:39.612 --> 00:53:40.530
Look over there.

00:53:41.031 --> 00:53:42.490
Just now,

00:53:42.574 --> 00:53:44.743
Mr. Kim and Min-hui went into that hotel.

00:53:45.243 --> 00:53:47.120
I saw them by chance and followed them.

00:53:51.875 --> 00:53:53.835
I wanted you to see it for yourself,

00:53:54.878 --> 00:53:56.379
since you wouldn't believe me.

00:53:58.423 --> 00:53:59.341
Mr. Heo!

00:53:59.883 --> 00:54:02.093
I told you, I saw them!
Why won't you believe me?

00:54:02.177 --> 00:54:03.887
Fine, you punk!

00:54:04.387 --> 00:54:06.598
Let's say you did see them. So what?

00:54:07.098 --> 00:54:10.352
What does such vulgar gossip
have to do with me?

00:54:13.104 --> 00:54:15.982
You dragged me here for this crap,
by lying, no less?

00:54:18.401 --> 00:54:19.486
I'm done with you.

00:54:19.569 --> 00:54:21.446
I can't waste any more of my time

00:54:21.946 --> 00:54:24.032
on this foolishness.

00:54:25.992 --> 00:54:29.037
I don't need this. Our lessons are over.

00:54:29.537 --> 00:54:30.663
Over!

00:54:34.918 --> 00:54:35.752
Oh my God!

00:54:35.835 --> 00:54:36.920
What the…

00:54:40.465 --> 00:54:42.675
Oh no, she's bleeding. Hurry!

00:55:06.658 --> 00:55:07.951
That's her.

00:55:10.412 --> 00:55:11.413
Min-hui.

00:55:12.872 --> 00:55:13.748
What did you say?

00:55:14.249 --> 00:55:15.625
An ambulance. Hurry!

00:55:23.633 --> 00:55:24.634
That's Mr. Kim.

00:55:25.135 --> 00:55:27.470
-She's bleeding.
-Where?

00:55:41.151 --> 00:55:41.985
That…

00:55:42.735 --> 00:55:44.988
That man is…

00:55:47.198 --> 00:55:48.408
Mr. Kim?

00:55:49.492 --> 00:55:50.785
Se-yun's dad?

00:55:52.829 --> 00:55:53.663
Yes.

00:56:19.355 --> 00:56:20.273
That man…

00:56:22.233 --> 00:56:23.401
is Mr. Kim?

00:56:48.968 --> 00:56:52.472
So you're Se-yun's new friend.
Nice to meet you. Lee Kang, right?

00:57:15.161 --> 00:57:16.412
Kim Su-hun.

00:57:18.039 --> 00:57:19.415
Kim Su-hun…

00:57:25.296 --> 00:57:26.714
is Se-yun's dad?

00:58:13.303 --> 00:58:16.306
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

01:00:42.410 --> 01:00:47.415
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi